      "target": {
        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(llm): preserve structured tool result text across providers",
        "body": "## Summary\n\nFixes #96857 by preserving structured non-image tool result content as text during provider context conversion instead of dropping it and falling back to `(see attached image)` / empty-output placeholders.\n\n## Problem\n\nTool results can contain structured content blocks from MCP-style resources, JSON/status payloads, or provider/runtime adapters. Several provider serializers only kept `type: \"text\"` blocks when converting tool results for model context. If a tool result had useful structured blocks but no plain text block, the agent-visible context could degrade to placeholders such as `(see attached image)` or provider-specific empty output fallbacks.\n\n## Changes\n\n- Adds a shared `extractToolResultText()` provider helper that:\n  - preserves normal text blocks;\n  - ignores image bytes for text extraction;\n  - serializes other structured non-image blocks as JSON text;\n  - redacts inline data URIs before serialization;\n  - keeps provider conversion lossless and leaves budgeting/truncation to existing context guards.\n- Applies the helper to provider context conversion paths for:\n  - OpenAI Chat Completions;\n  - OpenAI Responses / Responses transport replay;\n  - Anthropic Messages / Anthropic transport replay;\n  - Google Generative AI / Vertex conversion;\n  - Mistral Conversations.\n- Keeps image-capable payloads multimodal while adding structured/text context alongside images instead of replacing the text channel with an image placeholder.\n- Adds focused regression coverage for structured-only and mixed structured+image tool results.\n- Updates the changelog.\n\n## Verification\n\n- `git diff --check upstream/main...HEAD` ✅\n- Added focused regression tests covering structured tool result preservation across OpenAI, Anthropic, Google, and Mistral conversion paths.\n\nNot run locally: targeted Vitest suites were not executed in this checkout because dependencies are not installed (`node_modules` is absent). PR CI should provide the executable test proof.\n\n## Risk\n\nLow/medium. This only changes provider serialization of existing tool-result content. Structured non-image blocks now remain visible as JSON text; image bytes are still handled through existing image paths and inline data URIs inside structured strings are redacted before JSON serialization.\n\n",
